        "text_bCUG9t": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h2>The wines</h2><p>A carefully sequenced flight drawn from TerraVino's portfolio of small-production Italian estates; sparkling, whites, reds, or a journey through all, chosen to tell a coherent story as a group. The selection is tailored to your occasion and can be extended for groups who want to go deeper.</p><h2>The food</h2><p>The spread is deliberately cross-cultural. Alongside Italian charcuterie and aged cheeses, expect local favourites (or Japanese seafood, or perhaps Korean pancakes) and other carefully chosen bites that reflect Singapore's table as much as Italy's. Every pairing is chosen to complement the wines: sometimes in harmony, sometimes in deliberate contrast.</p><h2>The host</h2><p>Every TerraVino tasting is led by someone who knows these producers personally: their land, their methods, their choices. The conversation goes as deep as the table wants it to.</p>"
          }
        }
